
1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:06,360
ALHAMDU LILLAH, WA ASHHADU AN LA ILAHA ILLA ALLAH, WAHDAHU LA SHARIKA LAH

2
00:00:06,360 --> 00:00:08,174
Praise be to God

3
00:00:08,174 --> 00:00:11,756
and we bear witness that there is only one God.

4
00:00:13,097 --> 00:00:15,816
I want to start my Khutba,

5
00:00:15,816 --> 00:00:19,870
this time with the beautiful quotation from the Bible,

6
00:00:19,870 --> 00:00:23,377
from Luke 12: 29-31.

7
00:00:24,932 --> 00:00:28,839
It is, of course, a Quranic idea. The author is One and the same.

8
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:34,133
And this is expressed beautifully in English.

9
00:00:34,133 --> 00:00:41,549
Starting at 29, it says "it is not for you to be in search of what you are to eat or drink.

10
00:00:41,549 --> 00:00:43,922
Stop worrying.

11
00:00:43,922 --> 00:00:49,784
The unbelievers of this world are always running after these things.

12
00:00:49,784 --> 00:00:54,424
God knows that you need such things.

13
00:00:54,424 --> 00:00:58,349
Seek out, instead, His kingship over you.

14
00:00:58,349 --> 00:01:01,011
and the rest will follow, in turn." 

15
00:01:01,011 --> 00:01:08,256
So all you need to do is seek God's kingship over you and everything else you need, follows,

16
00:01:08,256 --> 00:01:12,515
the food, the provisions, the clothing, the health.

17
00:01:12,515 --> 00:01:14,541
Everything else follows.

18
00:01:14,541 --> 00:01:19,287
So, what does this mean? What does seeking God's kingship mean?

19
00:01:20,781 --> 00:01:24,861
It means that you give priority to God's commandments.

20
00:01:24,861 --> 00:01:28,367
You give priority to the 5 contact prayers.

21
00:01:28,367 --> 00:01:34,108
You wake up in the morning and you say "my duty today is to do the 5 contact prayers."

22
00:01:38,040 --> 00:01:43,924
That you... the Friday prayer is a commandment from God. There is a commandment in Sura 60, verse 9

23
00:01:43,924 --> 00:01:47,167
that you must go to the Friday prayer. You give this priority. 

24
00:01:47,167 --> 00:01:52,242
You arrange your life and your job and your circumstances

25
00:01:52,242 --> 00:01:56,430
so you will do the 5 daily prayers and the Friday prayer.

26
00:01:58,411 --> 00:02:01,379
And of course, you people here are the least people who need this. 

27
00:02:01,379 --> 00:02:05,757
Some people out there are the ones who need this kind of reminder.

28
00:02:07,616 --> 00:02:11,834
You put on the list of your priorities, the Quranic study. 

29
00:02:11,834 --> 00:02:18,297
There's a Quranic study, every Friday night, going on here, where we study the word of God

30
00:02:18,297 --> 00:02:21,044
and you have to work your circumstances.

31
00:02:21,044 --> 00:02:27,606
You cannot be somewhere in Tucson and there's a Quranic study going on somewhere in the mosque. 

32
00:02:27,606 --> 00:02:29,671
Otherwise, you don't really care.

33
00:02:29,671 --> 00:02:32,557
You're not seeking God's kingship over you, 

34
00:02:32,557 --> 00:02:36,923
to be sitting within, say 50 miles, 

35
00:02:36,923 --> 00:02:39,381
and there's a Quranic study going on.

36
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:47,649
What does it mean to seek God's kingship over you and everything else follows, the provisions, the health, the happiness?

37
00:02:48,777 --> 00:02:54,543
You give priority to the activities of the believers.

38
00:02:54,543 --> 00:03:02,707
You remember the verse in Sura 18 that say "force yourself to be with those who worship God Alone."

39
00:03:02,707 --> 00:03:06,356
Because it takes some effort and some work. It's not easy. 

40
00:03:06,356 --> 00:03:10,566
But this is what is good for you, as you will see in the second KHUTBAH, Insha Allah.

41
00:03:12,578 --> 00:03:14,326
It means that

42
00:03:14,326 --> 00:03:17,384
you make a point of giving out the ZAKAT charity

43
00:03:17,384 --> 00:03:18,746
as commanded by God.

44
00:03:18,746 --> 00:03:21,651
This is how you seek God's kingship over you

45
00:03:21,651 --> 00:03:31,113
one day in the year, whatever, January first, December 31st, the first day of Ramadan, any day you set for yourself,

46
00:03:31,113 --> 00:03:34,794
one day in the year, you calculate exactly how much you are worth

47
00:03:34,794 --> 00:03:39,555
and you give out 2.5% to people that you know personally,

48
00:03:39,555 --> 00:03:43,683
people who need your charity.

49
00:03:43,683 --> 00:03:46,318
And the Quran gives the exact order:

50
00:03:46,318 --> 00:03:49,775
your parents, first. If they don't need it, then your relatives 

51
00:03:49,775 --> 00:03:52,368
your cousins, your brothers, sisters.

52
00:03:52,368 --> 00:03:56,166
I mean your genetic brothers and sisters.

53
00:03:56,166 --> 00:04:01,167
And if all your relatives are rich, they don't need it, then you go to the orphans,

54
00:04:01,167 --> 00:04:03,549
children who have no support

55
00:04:03,549 --> 00:04:07,188
one of the parents is missing somehow

56
00:04:07,188 --> 00:04:11,911
and after that, the traveling stranger.

57
00:04:11,911 --> 00:04:17,283
Somebody stranded from Mexico or Nicaragua or whatever and passes by your house

58
00:04:17,283 --> 00:04:18,455
or you know personally

59
00:04:18,455 --> 00:04:25,117
people who immigrated from Thailand or Vietnam and they're living in a house in a terrible conditions and you know them.

60
00:04:25,117 --> 00:04:27,431
Then, they come next.

61
00:04:27,431 --> 00:04:33,163
So, there is a specific sequence or order to give out this charity.

62
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:39,198
You give priority to Hajj eventually

63
00:04:39,198 --> 00:04:41,857
not now. I wouldn't advise you to do it now.

64
00:04:41,857 --> 00:04:44,397
The Quran makes it conditional.

65
00:04:44,397 --> 00:04:50,735
Someday all of us, Insha Allah, will go. We're gonna charter a plane when we'll go, all of us. We'll make Hajj. 

66
00:04:50,735 --> 00:04:56,063
And we'll go in as will be great victory because the land over there will be worshiping God alone.

67
00:04:56,063 --> 00:05:00,881
This is God's promise to us and therefore, I can talk about it in this way.

68
00:05:00,881 --> 00:05:04,430
So eventually, you'll have to observe Hajj. 

69
00:05:06,259 --> 00:05:09,250
You seek God's kingship over you, 

70
00:05:09,250 --> 00:05:14,286
and everything else follows by observing the prohibitions that God gave you.

71
00:05:14,286 --> 00:05:20,345
You don't drink. You don't gamble. You don't eat pork. 

72
00:05:20,345 --> 00:05:24,610
You don't lie. You don't cheat.  

73
00:05:24,610 --> 00:05:27,730
You don't violate your promises. 

74
00:05:27,730 --> 00:05:29,613
You must be a person of your word. 

75
00:05:29,613 --> 00:05:33,730
You must be an example of a person of God,

76
00:05:33,730 --> 00:05:36,473
one, a member in God's kingdom. 

77
00:05:43,606 --> 00:05:48,846
Anything else in your life must take place number two. 

78
00:05:48,846 --> 00:05:52,536
You give priority to these activities, the commands of God  

79
00:05:52,536 --> 00:05:55,187
and this way you seek God's kingship over you

80
00:05:55,187 --> 00:05:58,464
and this way you attain all other goals:

81
00:05:58,464 --> 00:06:04,370
money, health, wealth, happiness, etc., etc. 

82
00:06:04,370 --> 00:06:06,939
TUBU ILLA ALLAH. Repent. 

83
00:06:17,912 --> 00:06:23,073
ALHAMDU LILLAH, WA ASHHADU AN LA ILAHA ILLA ALLAH, WAHDAHU LA SHARIKA LAH.

84
00:06:25,999 --> 00:06:30,088
By studying the Quran continuously, we have discovered the secret of happiness.

85
00:06:32,405 --> 00:06:36,600
The secret of happiness is a developed, nourished and grown soul,

86
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:39,544
the real you, the real person, not this body. 

87
00:06:40,794 --> 00:06:42,658
This is the secret of happiness. 

88
00:06:42,658 --> 00:06:48,153
And we came to this conclusion by studying people who obtained everything. 

89
00:06:48,153 --> 00:06:51,305
They got everything that the human beings go after: 

90
00:06:51,305 --> 00:06:57,502
money, fame, good looks, sports cars, whatever. 

91
00:06:57,502 --> 00:07:00,977
And I have used the example of Eddie Murphy,

92
00:07:00,977 --> 00:07:04,286
a movie star when he was interviewed by Barbara Walters

93
00:07:04,286 --> 00:07:12,795
He's got millions of dollars. He's got palaces in California, exclusive places and in New Jersey,

94
00:07:12,795 --> 00:07:15,416
the five luxurious cars,

95
00:07:15,416 --> 00:07:21,514
all the girls, all the money, all the fame that he wants.

96
00:07:21,514 --> 00:07:23,859
And he told Barbara Walters he was not happy.

97
00:07:23,859 --> 00:07:25,883
So, what is the secret of happiness?

98
00:07:25,883 --> 00:07:28,316
Aren't these the things that people are going after

99
00:07:28,316 --> 00:07:31,460
money and fame and wealth and whatever?

100
00:07:31,460 --> 00:07:33,490
And he is not happy. 

101
00:07:33,490 --> 00:07:38,674
So, the secret of happiness is that he must develop his soul.

102
00:07:38,674 --> 00:07:43,414
And the soul can be developed by worshiping God alone.

103
00:07:45,304 --> 00:07:51,854
Now, this KHUTBA, I want to talk about God's name: AL-RAZAQ, the provider.

104
00:07:51,854 --> 00:07:53,111
The provider.

105
00:07:53,111 --> 00:07:57,519
God is the exclusive provider.  

106
00:07:57,519 --> 00:08:04,718
He is the one who decides how much money you're going to make, or you made from birth to death. 

107
00:08:04,718 --> 00:08:10,724
And I want to shed a whole new light on this word "the provider"

108
00:08:10,724 --> 00:08:14,650
because God provides for the body and for the soul.

109
00:08:16,144 --> 00:08:23,117
Therefore, the contact prayers that you do five times a day are a provision from God. 

110
00:08:24,702 --> 00:08:29,697
The duties that I talked about in the first KHUTBA, they're actually a gift from God. 

111
00:08:29,697 --> 00:08:36,012
And we see this... there's a lot of evidence in the Quran for this. 

112
00:08:38,115 --> 00:08:41,167
For example, in Sura 7, verse 43,

113
00:08:41,167 --> 00:08:43,397
we see that the people in Heaven 

114
00:08:43,397 --> 00:08:48,000
pray and say "ALHAMDU LILLAH", "Praise be to God" who guided us to this.

115
00:08:48,172 --> 00:08:52,543
We could not, we could never be guided without God's blessing and guiding us."

116
00:08:52,543 --> 00:08:55,669
In other words, it was not their doing.

117
00:08:55,669 --> 00:09:00,320
It is God's blessing and God's gift to them that guided them.

118
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:03,891
In sura 10, verse 9, 

119
00:09:03,891 --> 00:09:06,526
we see a very clear principle

120
00:09:06,526 --> 00:09:12,476
saying that God guides the people because of their faith or their belief.

121
00:09:12,476 --> 00:09:18,469
 In other words, when you decide to worship God alone, then God provides for your soul

122
00:09:18,469 --> 00:09:22,709
and God provides the five contact prayers for your soul

123
00:09:22,709 --> 00:09:26,242
and the fasting of the month of Ramadan for your soul.

124
00:09:26,242 --> 00:09:29,668
I mean, you think that you're gonna do the five contact prayers,

125
00:09:29,668 --> 00:09:34,329
but really it's a gift from God. You cannot do it without God's guidance. 

126
00:09:34,329 --> 00:09:38,928
Sura 9 verse 10. Sura 10, verse 9, excuse me. 

127
00:09:38,928 --> 00:09:42,663
In sura 49, verse 17, 

128
00:09:42,663 --> 00:09:44,802
another clear evidence for this. 

129
00:09:44,802 --> 00:09:53,704
The verse says "they act as if they are doing you a favor by embracing Islam or by practicing Islam

130
00:09:53,704 --> 00:10:01,279
instead, God is the one who blessed them by guiding them to Islam."

131
00:10:01,279 --> 00:10:07,274
So, when we worship God alone, when we do the five daily prayers, when we fast the month of Ramadan, 

132
00:10:07,274 --> 00:10:12,106
when we join the Quranic study and even the picnics of the Muslim group,

133
00:10:12,106 --> 00:10:16,203
we are not doing God a favor. 

134
00:10:16,203 --> 00:10:19,104
It is God's provisions to our souls. 

135
00:10:22,487 --> 00:10:26,469
In sura 14, verse 40, we see Abraham praying

136
00:10:26,469 --> 00:10:27,930
and what is he saying?

137
00:10:27,930 --> 00:10:32,234
He says, "please God make me an observer of the Contact Prayers"

138
00:10:32,234 --> 00:10:35,266
because it's a gift from God.

139
00:10:35,266 --> 00:10:38,502
"and also my children" he said. 

140
00:10:38,502 --> 00:10:44,737
He said "please God make me an observer of the Contact Prayers."

141
00:10:44,737 --> 00:10:47,062
رَبِّ ٱجْعَلْنِى مُقِيمَ ٱلصَّلَوٰةِ (14:40) 

142
00:10:47,062 --> 00:10:48,520
in Arabic.

143
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:50,757
He didn't say, "please, God give me a million dollars."

144
00:10:52,860 --> 00:10:58,037
So, observing the five Contact Prayers is a privilege, and a gift and a blessing.

145
00:10:58,037 --> 00:11:00,899
It is not a hardship. It is not work. 

146
00:11:00,899 --> 00:11:04,753
You get up for the morning prayer, before sunrise, 

147
00:11:04,753 --> 00:11:11,763
not because you want to do this, or because you're doing such a great effort, you know, for God's sake.

148
00:11:11,763 --> 00:11:15,015
It's because God blessed you and enabled you 

149
00:11:15,015 --> 00:11:18,820
to get up before sunrise to feed your soul,

150
00:11:18,820 --> 00:11:22,099
this very important meal, the morning prayer. 

151
00:11:24,842 --> 00:11:30,974
Abraham said " رَبِّ ٱجْعَلْنِى مُقِيمَ ٱلصَّلَوٰةِ" My Lord, make me one who observes the Contact Prayers,

152
00:11:30,974 --> 00:11:33,538
and also my children.

153
00:11:37,165 --> 00:11:42,546
People in Satan's kingdom are provided with sins. 

154
00:11:46,752 --> 00:11:49,347
We see this in Sura 24, verse 21.

155
00:11:49,347 --> 00:11:53,517
When Satan collects people in his kingdom,

156
00:11:53,517 --> 00:11:57,488
he pushes them to go to the bar and lie and cheat, 

157
00:11:57,488 --> 00:12:03,345
and drink and do not feed your soul. 

158
00:12:03,345 --> 00:12:10,167
This is what sins are: not feeding the soul, depriving the soul, poverty of the soul.

159
00:12:10,167 --> 00:12:14,501
On the other hand, in Sura 7, verse 28,

160
00:12:14,501 --> 00:12:19,250
we see the principle that God does not advocate vice. 

161
00:12:24,340 --> 00:12:27,275
So, it's the exact opposite of what Satan does.

162
00:12:27,275 --> 00:12:33,322
And this is why I want to remind you again that God never ordered Abraham to slaughter his son

163
00:12:33,322 --> 00:12:36,601
because this is a terrible vice, of course. 

164
00:12:36,601 --> 00:12:43,956
And this is why we never, never find it in the Quran that Abraham ordered Abraham to sacrifice his son.

165
00:12:43,956 --> 00:12:53,729
That wouldn't make sense and it does not... this law that "God does not advocate sins" would be violated. 

166
00:13:04,336 --> 00:13:09,229
People in Satan's kingdom, because of their idol worship, 

167
00:13:09,229 --> 00:13:14,460
they may observe the five Contact Prayers, but they do not make contact. 

168
00:13:14,460 --> 00:13:15,608
They dial the wrong number. 

169
00:13:17,406 --> 00:13:21,311
They dial Satan's number because they mention other names with God. 

170
00:13:21,311 --> 00:13:23,765
And this is a trick of Satan.

171
00:13:23,765 --> 00:13:29,384
And this is why we find in the Quran such statements as "woe to those who observe the Salat prayers."

172
00:13:29,384 --> 00:13:31,668
وَيْلٌ لِلْمُصَلِّينَ (107:4)

173
00:13:33,283 --> 00:13:36,581
Because, now they are really doing an effort,

174
00:13:36,581 --> 00:13:41,270
but it's all in vain. As we see in Sura 39, it is all in vain. 

175
00:13:41,270 --> 00:13:47,684
Once there is a name mentioned with God in the prayer, it violates the commandment in Sura 72, verse 18.

176
00:13:47,684 --> 00:13:54,922
Once another name is mentioned, the whole effort is in vain. 

177
00:13:54,922 --> 00:13:56,513
And we are blessed here.

178
00:13:56,513 --> 00:13:58,974
See, we're gonna stand up, we're gonna pray to God, 

179
00:13:58,974 --> 00:14:03,426
we're gonna establish contact with God,

180
00:14:03,426 --> 00:14:05,343
and there will be no name.

181
00:14:05,343 --> 00:14:08,790
From the moment we say, "ALLAH-O AKBAR" (God is the greatest) to open the prayer to the end, 

182
00:14:08,790 --> 00:14:10,794
there'll be no name but the name of God. 

183
00:14:12,958 --> 00:14:15,583
And you can see the difference. 

184
00:14:15,583 --> 00:14:18,857
AQEM AL-SALAT (let's observe Salat prayer)

185
00:14:18,857 --> 00:14:22,784
ALLAH-O AKBAR, ALLAH-O AKBAR, LA ILAAHA ILLAA ALLAH. (God is the greatest, God is the greatest. There is not god but one God.)

186
00:14:22,784 --> 00:14:27,700
ALLAH-O AKBAR (God is the greatest)

